[Human West Nile virus (WNV) infections with serious disease occur sporadically in Israel. The 1st cases were recognized there in the 1950s. The largest outbreak in humans in Israel, with 439 serologically-confirmed cases and 29 deaths, occurred in 2000, with a 73 per cent rate of neuroinvasive disease in hospitalised patients. As in other areas within the WNV geographic range, its wildlife reservoirs are wild birds, and it is transmitted by _Culex_ mosquitoes. Equine animals may also develop clinical disease when infected.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail of Israel can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2680134,90. - Mod.TY]
